# YouTube Arabic Transcriber ğŸ¬

A Streamlit web application that automatically transcribes Arabic YouTube videos and translates them to English using OpenAI's Whisper AI and Google Translate.

## ğŸŒŸ Features

- **Batch Processing**: Process multiple YouTube videos at once
- **Arabic Transcription**: High-quality Arabic speech-to-text using Whisper AI
- **English Translation**: Automatic translation using Google Translate
- **Download Results**: Export all transcripts as organized text files
- **User-friendly Interface**: Clean, intuitive Streamlit web interface

## ğŸš€ Live Demo

Access the live app here: [YouTube Arabic Transcriber](https://your-app-name.streamlit.app)

## ğŸ› ï¸ Installation

### Local Setup

1. Clone the repository:
```bash
git clone https://github.com/trishbailey/youtube-arabic-transcriber.git
cd youtube-arabic-transcriber
```

2. Create a virtual environment:
```bash
python -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate  # On Windows: venv\Scripts\activate
```

3. Install dependencies:
```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

4. Run the app:
```bash
streamlit run app.py
```

## ğŸ“± Usage

1. **Enter YouTube URLs**: Paste one or more YouTube video URLs in the sidebar
2. **Start Processing**: Click "Start Processing" to begin transcription
3. **View Results**: See Arabic transcripts and English translations side-by-side
4. **Download**: Export all results as organized text files

## ğŸ”§ Technical Details

- **Speech Recognition**: OpenAI Whisper (large model for best Arabic accuracy)
- **Translation**: Google Translate API
- **Video Download**: yt-dlp for robust YouTube video downloading
- **Frontend**: Streamlit for the web interface

## ğŸ“‹ Requirements

- Python 3.8+
- FFmpeg (for audio processing)
- Internet connection (for downloading videos and translation)

## ğŸš¨ Limitations

- Processing time depends on video length and server resources
- Large videos may take several minutes to process
- Free Streamlit hosting has memory and processing limitations

